		<RECORD id="0-0-0-219910" number="6738" version="1673">
			<HEADING>Chapter 7: Discriminatory Boycotts</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2157" name="T08C007"/>Chapter 7: Discriminatory Boycotts</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
			<RECORD id="0-0-0-5244" number="6739" version="1673">
				<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
					<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 1991/039" destination-id="0-0-0-26706">L.L. 1991/039</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-085]</HIGHLIGHTER>
				</PARA>
			</RECORD>
		</LEVEL>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-688" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Appendix" style-name-escaped="Appendix" style-id="0-0-0-691" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-694" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Article" style-name-escaped="Article" style-id="0-0-0-697" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle" style-name-escaped="Subarticle" style-id="0-0-0-700" level-depth="7" toc-section="false">
							<LEVEL style-name="Subarticle - Part" style-name-escaped="Subarticle---Part" style-id="0-0-0-29474" level-depth="8" toc-section="false">
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-219911" number="6740" version="1673">
										<HEADING>§ 8-701 Legislative declaration. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2159" name="8-701"/>§ 8-701 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Legislative declaration. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5245" number="6741" version="3">
											<PARA>Boycotts or blacklists that are based on a person&apos;s race, color, creed, age, national origin, alienage or citizenship status, marital status, partnership status, gender, sexual orientation, or disability pose a menace to the city&apos;s foundation and institutions. In contrast to protests that are in reaction to an unlawful discriminatory practice, connected with a labor dispute or associated with other speech or activities that are protected by the first amendment discriminatory boycotts cause havoc, divide the citizenry and do not serve a legitimate purpose. The council declares that discriminatory boycotts are a dangerously insidious form of prejudice and hereby establishes a procedure for expeditiously investigating allegations of this type of prejudice, assuring that the council and mayor are duly alerted to the existence of such activity and combating discriminatory boycotts or blacklists.</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5246" number="6742" version="1673">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">
													<BOOKMARK id="0-0-0-24542" name=""/>Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 1991/039" destination-id="0-0-0-26706">L.L. 1991/039</LINK> and <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 2005/085" destination-id="0-0-0-25158">L.L. 2005/085</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-085]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-209374" number="6743" version="1466">
										<HEADING>§ 8-702 Definitions. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2161" name="8-702"/>§ 8-702 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Definitions. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5247" number="6744" version="3">
											<PARA>As used in this chapter, the following terms have the following meanings: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5248" number="6745" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Commission.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;commission&quot; means the city commission on human rights. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5249" number="6746" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Council.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;council&quot; means the council of the city of New York. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5250" number="6747" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Discriminatory boycott or blacklist.</CHARFORMAT> The term &quot;discriminatory boycott or blacklist&quot; means any act that is an unlawful discriminatory practice under subdivision 18 of section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="8-107" destination-id="0-0-0-2045">8-107</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5251" number="6748" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5252" number="6749" version="1673">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 1991/039" destination-id="0-0-0-26706">L.L. 1991/039</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-085]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
								<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-703" level-depth="9" toc-section="true">
									<RECORD id="0-0-0-219912" number="6750" version="1673">
										<HEADING>§ 8-703 Investigative reporting requirements. </HEADING>
										<PARA>
											<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-2163" name="8-703"/>§ 8-703 <CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Investigative reporting requirements. </CHARFORMAT>
										</PARA>
									</RECORD>
									<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5253" number="6751" version="3">
											<PARA>The following requirements shall apply to all complaints alleging that a discriminatory boycott or blacklist is occurring: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5254" number="6752" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The commission shall begin an investigation within 24 hours of the filing of a complaint which alleges that a discriminatory boycott or blacklist is occurring. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5255" number="6753" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Within three days after initiating such an investigation, the commission shall file a written report with the mayor. The report shall state: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5256" number="6754" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The allegations contained in the complaint; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5257" number="6755" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whether the commission has reason to believe a discriminatory boycott or blacklist is taking place; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5258" number="6756" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Steps the commission has taken to resolve the dispute. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5259" number="6757" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If it is stated within the report described in subdivision 2 of this section that the commission has reason to believe that a discriminatory boycott or blacklist has taken place, within 30 days after filing such report, the commission shall file a second report with the mayor and the council. This second report shall contain: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5260" number="6758" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A brief description of the allegations contained in the complaint; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5261" number="6759" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A determination of whether probable cause exists to believe a discriminatory boycott or blacklist is taking place; <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5262" number="6760" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A recitation of the facts that form the basis of the commission&apos;s determination of probable cause; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5263" number="6761" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If the boycott or blacklist is continuing at the date of the report, a description of all actions the commission or other city agency has taken or will undertake to resolve the dispute. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5264" number="6762" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(4)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If a finding of probable cause is not contained in the report required by subdivision 3 of this section and the boycott or blacklist continues for more than 20 days subsequent to the report&apos;s release, then, upon demand of the mayor or council, the commission shall update such report. Report updates shall detail: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5265" number="6763" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whether or not the commission presently has probable cause to believe a discriminatory boycott or blacklist is taking place; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5266" number="6764" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>All new activity the commission or other city agency has taken or will undertake to resolve the dispute. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5267" number="6765" version="3">
											<PARA>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>(5)<TAB tab-count="1"/>If the commission determines that the disclosure of any information in a report required by this section may interfere with or compromise a pending investigation or efforts to resolve the dispute by mediation or conciliation, it shall file the report without such information and state in the report the reasons for omitting such information. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-5268" number="6766" version="3">
											<PARA>(Am. L.L. 2018/063, 1/19/2018, eff. 10/16/2018) <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-219914" number="6767" version="1673">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> For related unconsolidated provisions, see Appendix A at <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="L.L. 1991/039" destination-id="0-0-0-26706">L.L. 1991/039</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-085]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
										<RECORD id="0-0-0-219915" number="6768" version="1673">
											<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-18">
												<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> The following former provisions of this Title 8 have been renumbered by L.L. 2018/063 as follows: <HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
												<LINEBRK/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>Chapter 8: Prevention of Interference With Reproductive Health Services – See <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="T10C010" destination-id="0-0-0-2165">Title 10, Chapter 10</LINK>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
												<LINEBRK/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>Chapter 9: Actions By Victims of Gender-Motivated Violence – See <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="T10C011" destination-id="0-0-0-2167">Title 10, Chapter 11</LINK>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
												<LINEBRK/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>Chapter 10: Equal Access to Human Services – See <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="T21C001S01" destination-id="0-0-0-2169">Title 21, Chapter 1, Subchapter 1</LINK>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
												<LINEBRK/>
												<TAB tab-count="1"/>Chapter 11: Reports on Discipline and Certain Emergency Transports of Students – See <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-23" type="Jump" destination-name="T21-aC019" destination-id="0-0-0-2171">Title 21-A, Chapter 19</LINK>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="ALP" style-name-escaped="ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-25">[ALP S-030]</HIGHLIGHTER>
											</PARA>
										</RECORD>
									</LEVEL>
								</LEVEL>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
